external_knowledge:
- 'Completed' refers to surveys and readings that have been fully executed and are considered final;
- 'Survey details' include the survey ID, survey name, survey date, status, location name, project name, and equipment name;
- 'Reading details' include the reading ID, location, RL value, resistivity, conductivity, depth, time, line type, start point, end point, length, and line status.

- 'The three most recent voyages' refers to the top 3 surveys based on the `survey_date` in descending order;
- 'The names and types of the guiding lighthouses' refers to the `equipment_name` and `equipment_type` of the equipment used;
- 'The latest version of the map' refers to the `latest_version_date` of the survey version.

- Each survey can have multiple versions;
- The `version_date` indicates when a version was created;
- `equipment_name` is derived from the `equipment` table using `equipment_id`.

- 'Completed' surveys are those that have been fully conducted and recorded in the database;
- 'Resistivity' is a measure of how strongly a material opposes the flow of electric current;
- 'Location 1' is a specific site where surveys are conducted.

sql:
SELECT resistivity
FROM survey_readings
WHERE resistivity > 10.0;

external_knowledge:
- Resistivity readings are measurements taken during surveys to assess the resistance of materials or soil;
- Each resistivity reading has a unique identifier (`resistivity_id`) and can have multiple versions (`version_id`);
- The `version_date` indicates when each version of the resistivity reading was created;
- Surveys are conducted using specific equipment, identified by `equipment_id`.

